org.batfish.datamodel.questions

Class Exclusion

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.batfish.datamodel.questions.Exclusion

  • public class Exclusion
extends java.lang.Object
    Describes rows to be excluded in a TableAnswerElement. An Exclusion may "cover" multiple rows and cause them to be excluded.

      • firstCoversSecond

        public static boolean firstCoversSecond(com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.JsonNode first,
                                        com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.JsonNode second)
        Evaluates if the first object covers the second object. For it to be true, the two objects should be of the same type and

        i) If the type is atomic (e.g., string), should have equal values

        ii) If the type is list, each element in the first object should cover some element in the second. ['a'] covers ['a', 'b'] but not the other way around.

        iii) If the type is map, each key in the first object should be present in the second object and the corresponding first value should cover the second value. {'k1' : 'v1' } covers {'k1' : 'v1', 'k2': 'v2'} but not the other way around.

        Parameters:
        first - The first object
        second - The second object
        Returns:
        Results of the evaluation
